main event: Two unidentified flying objects were observed by multiple witnesses in the St. Paul, Minnesota area on March 22, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were observed by a farmer and his 20-year-old son for about 7 minutes.
Another sighting was reported by a woman and her 12-year-old daughter, who described the object as a bright light that hovered in front of their car, causing the car's lights to go out.
The objects were described as having red, green, and bright white lights, and were seen to move at very high speeds.
The Air Force investigated the sightings and determined they were likely caused by USAF anti-submarine patrol aircraft using high-intensity searchlights, as well as experimental hot air balloons.
The report notes that no positive identification could be made, but the Air Force believed the sightings could be explained by the known aircraft and balloon activities in the area.
witnesses: a farmer and his son, a woman and her daughter
